l mobility was a cause of the Mexican Revolution of 1910. Comparing Mexican practices with those in several East Asian countries also allows Camp to question many of the tenets of political recruitment theory. His book will be of interest to students not only of Mexican politics but also of history, comparative politics, political leadership, and Third World development.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/71172340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292733626423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292733626/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK